```

Reasons:
- `App.tsx` already owns all file-lifecycle state. Adding a parallel parsed view is consistent with how `fileContent` and `wordCount` are managed.
- The `PropertiesPanel` component will receive `parsedFrontmatter` as a prop ŌĆö no context or external store needed at this scale.
- Frontmatter is per-file; it gets reset on file switch, which already happens in `handleSelectFile`.

The update path in `handleSelectFile`:

```
const { frontmatter, body } = parseFrontmatter(raw);
frontmatterRef.current = frontmatter;
setFileContent(body);
setParsedFrontmatter(parseYamlFrontmatter(raw)); // new line
```

Also reset in `handleOpenWorkspace` and clear when no file is selected:

```
setParsedFrontmatter({});
```

**No write-back path for now** ŌĆö the properties panel is read-only in this iteration.

### 4. New Component: `src/components/PropertiesPanel.tsx`

**UI placement: inline "properties bar" above the editor, collapsible.**

Rationale given the "minimal chrome" principle:
- A right sidebar would permanently narrow the 680 px prose column, which fights the typography-first principle. It would also require a second resizable pane.
- An inline bar above the editor sits inside the `editor-wrapper` column, collapses to zero height when closed, and does not touch the prose width.
- The bar is only visible when a file is open and has frontmatter. If the file has no frontmatter at all (empty `{}`) the bar renders nothing ŌĆö zero chrome for plain files.
- A small toggle button at the top-right of the editor area (or a keyboard shortcut, e.g. `Cmd+Shift+P`) collapses/expands it.

**Layout of the bar:**

The bar renders fields as a horizontal pill row for a compact footprint. Common fields get a fixed display label; unknown fields show their raw key name. The ordering convention: `title` first (if present), then `date`, `tags`, then any remaining fields alphabetically.

Field rendering rules:
- `title` ŌĆö rendered as plain text (it's often redundant with the H1 but still useful to see).
- `date` ŌĆö formatted as a human-readable date string using `Intl.DateTimeFormat`.
- `tags` ŌĆö rendered as individual tag chips.
- `draft: true` ŌĆö rendered as a "Draft" badge with a distinct background.
- All other string/number values ŌĆö `key: value` as monospaced pill.
- `null` or empty array ŌĆö field is skipped silently.

**Props:**

```ts
interface PropertiesPanelProps {
  frontmatter: ParsedFrontmatter;
  isOpen: boolean;
  onToggle: () => void;
}
```

The `isOpen` toggle state lives in `App.tsx` as `const [propertiesOpen, setPropertiesOpen] = useState(true)`. It persists across file switches (user preference) but defaults to open so first-time users see it.

### 5. Wiring in `App.tsx`

The `Editor` column (`editor-wrapper`) currently renders `<Editor .../>` directly. After this change the JSX structure becomes:

```tsx
<div className="editor-column">
  {selectedFile && Object.keys(parsedFrontmatter).length > 0 && (
    <PropertiesPanel
      frontmatter={parsedFrontmatter}
      isOpen={propertiesOpen}
      onToggle={() => setPropertiesOpen(v => !v)}
    />
  )}
  <Editor
    key={selectedFile?.path ?? "empty"}
    content={fileContent}
    onWordCount={setWordCount}
    onChange={handleEditorChange}
  />
</div>
```

The `.editor-column` wrapper is a new `flex-direction: column` div that replaces the bare `<Editor>` in the `.app-body` flex row. This div takes `flex: 1` so the sidebar width stays unchanged.

### 6. CSS for `PropertiesPanel`

Add to `src/App.css` (keeping all properties-panel styles co-located with the rest of the app shell).

Key design decisions:
- The bar uses `var(--color-bg-sidebar)` as its background ŌĆö slightly off the main editor white ŌĆö to visually separate it from prose without being heavy.
- A `1px` bottom border using `var(--color-border)` provides the divider line.
- Font is `var(--font-ui)` at `12px` ŌĆö clearly distinct from the serif editor font.
- Height animates with `max-height` transition (collapsed = `0`, expanded = `56px` or `auto` clamped by the constraint). Using `max-height` avoids JS-measured height calculations.
- Tag chips use `var(--color-accent-light)` background and `var(--color-accent)` text, consistent with the sidebar selected-file treatment.
- The "Draft" badge uses an amber/warning tone ŌĆö there is no amber token today, so add `--color-warning: #f59e0b` and `--color-warning-light: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.12)` to both `:root` and `[data-theme="dark"]` in `global.css`.
- The toggle button is a small `ŌĆ║` / `ŌĆ╣` chevron using `var(--color-text-faint)`, matching the sidebar icon style.

```css
/* ŌöĆŌöĆ Properties Panel ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ */
.editor-column {
  flex: 1;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  overflow: hidden;
}

.properties-panel {
  background: var(--color-bg-sidebar);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  overflow: hidden;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  transition: max-height 0.2s ease;
}

.properties-panel.open {
  max-height: 56px;
}

.properties-panel.closed {
  max-height: 0;
  border-bottom-color: transparent;
}

.properties-inner {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 8px;
  padding: 0 24px;
  height: 56px;
  max-width: 728px; /* 680px prose + 24px├Ś2 padding */
  margin: 0 auto;
  overflow: hidden;
}

.prop-field {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 4px;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.prop-label {
  font-size: 11px;
  color: var(--color-text-faint);
  font-family: var(--font-ui);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.04em;
}

.prop-value {
  font-size: 12px;
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
  font-family: var(--font-ui);
}

.prop-tag {
  font-size: 11px;
  color: var(--color-accent);
  background: var(--color-accent-light);
  border-radius: 4px;
  padding: 1px 6px;
  font-family: var(--font-ui);
}

.prop-draft {
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--color-warning);
  background: var(--color-warning-light);
  border-radius: 4px;
  padding: 1px 6px;
  font-family: var(--font-ui);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.04em;
}

.properties-toggle {
  position: absolute;
  right: 14px;
  top: 50%;
  transform: translateY(-50%);
  font-size: 13px;
  color: var(--color-text-faint);
  padding: 2px 4px;
  border-radius: 4px;
  transition: color 0.15s, background 0.15s;
}

.properties-toggle:hover {
  color: var(--color-accent);
  background: var(--color-accent-light);
}
```

The `.properties-inner` max-width of `728px` (= 680 + 48px horizontal padding) aligns the field row with the ProseMirror column so the content feels horizontally anchored to the prose text.

The toggle button should be placed outside `.properties-inner` in a `position: relative` wrapper so it stays pinned right regardless of the field overflow.

For the collapsed state, the toggle button itself remains visible (height ~24px) as a thin strip, letting the user re-open the panel. Alternatively (and cleaner), the toggle can live permanently in the status bar as a small icon ŌĆö but that requires touching `StatusBar.tsx` and creates a non-obvious connection. Recommended: keep it as a thin visible strip above the editor.

### 7. Summary of File Changes

| File | Change |
|---|---|
| `src/lib/frontmatter.ts` | Add `FrontmatterValue`, `ParsedFrontmatter` types; add `parseYamlFrontmatter()` function using `js-yaml` |
| `src/lib/types.ts` | Optionally re-export `ParsedFrontmatter` here for co-location with other shared types |
| `src/App.tsx` | Add `parsedFrontmatter` state; call `parseYamlFrontmatter` in `handleSelectFile`; add `propertiesOpen` toggle state; wrap `<Editor>` in `.editor-column` div; conditionally render `<PropertiesPanel>` |
| `src/components/PropertiesPanel.tsx` | New component ŌĆö renders structured fields as a horizontal pill row |
| `src/App.css` | Add `.editor-column`, `.properties-panel`, `.properties-inner`, `.prop-*` CSS |
| `src/styles/global.css` | Add `--color-warning` and `--color-warning-light` tokens to both `:root` and `[data-theme="dark"]` |
| `package.json` | Add `js-yaml` dependency (and `@types/js-yaml` as devDependency) |

### 8. Sequencing

1. Install `js-yaml` (`bun add js-yaml && bun add -d @types/js-yaml`).
2. Extend `src/lib/frontmatter.ts` with the types and `parseYamlFrontmatter` ŌĆö this is pure logic with no UI dependencies, testable in isolation.
3. Add warning color tokens to `src/styles/global.css`.
4. Add CSS classes for the panel to `src/App.css`.
5. Create `src/components/PropertiesPanel.tsx`.
6. Wire everything in `src/App.tsx` ŌĆö last because it depends on all of the above.
7. Type-check: `bun tsc --noEmit`.

### 9. Anticipated Issues

- **`js-yaml` bare date parsing**: `js-yaml` by default parses `date: 2024-01-15` as a JavaScript `Date` object. The `parseYamlFrontmatter` function must convert these to ISO strings before returning, otherwise React will throw on rendering a `Date` directly.
- **`js-yaml` schema**: Use `js-yaml`'s `DEFAULT_SCHEMA` (not `JSON_SCHEMA`) to preserve boolean coercion (`yes`/`no`/`true`/`false`) which Amytis frontmatter may use for `draft`.
- **Panel height with multi-line values**: If an unusual file has a very long `tags` array, the single-row layout will overflow. Add `overflow: hidden` with `text-overflow: ellipsis` on the inner row, or cap tags shown at N with a `+N more` chip.
- **`editor-wrapper` refactor**: The existing `.editor-wrapper` class in `editor.css` has `flex: 1`. Adding the new `.editor-column` wrapper above it means you must ensure `.editor-column` also has `flex: 1` and `overflow: hidden`, and that `.editor-wrapper` inside it still gets `flex: 1`. Check that the `.editor-scroll` padding (currently `48px 0`) still looks right with the panel above it.

---

### Critical Files for Implementation

- `/Users/hutusi/workspace/ai/naive/ovid-app/src/lib/frontmatter.ts` ŌĆö Core logic file where YAML parsing function and types are added; all other changes flow from what this exports.
- `/Users/hutusi/workspace/ai/naive/ovid-app/src/App.tsx` ŌĆö Owns all global state; requires new `parsedFrontmatter` and `propertiesOpen` state, updated `handleSelectFile`, and updated JSX layout to introduce the panel.
- `/Users/hutusi/workspace/ai/naive/ovid-app/src/App.css` ŌĆö All new panel CSS goes here; must also add the `.editor-column` wrapper class and ensure it does not disturb the existing flex layout.
- `/Users/hutusi/workspace/ai/naive/ovid-app/src/styles/global.css` ŌĆö New `--color-warning` / `--color-warning-light` tokens must be added to both `:root` and `[data-theme="dark"]` blocks for the draft badge to respect theme.
- `/Users/hutusi/workspace/ai/naive/ovid-app/src/styles/editor.css` ŌĆö Must verify that `.editor-wrapper` still receives `flex: 1` correctly inside the new `.editor-column` parent, particularly that `padding: 48px 0` on `.editor-scroll` does not create awkward double-spacing with the panel above it.

